\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Could you give me your full name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Alfred Henry Pyle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 8, Abbots Close, Onslow Village, Guildford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And the year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - just a minute - 1915 - 1915.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 1890.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 In Guildford. Er - let me see - Charlotteville area - up there - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 About four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And then you moved to ......?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Walnut tree close - Guildford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And you stayed there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Until I joined the Army in 1915.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Why did the family make this move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, my father worked on the railway and Walnut Tree Close is very close to the station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How many brothers and sisters did you' have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I had one sister only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was she older than yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No - she was two years younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How old was your father when you were born? Do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I'm sorry, but.....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would he be a young man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he marry later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No - oh - er - sort of usual age I think. Er - how can I get at it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Wiltshire - near Salisbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 He was a clerk on railway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he have another job before he did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, so far as I know, no other job - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And what about afterwards - did he change his work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no. He stayed there 'til he was pensioned off. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he do any part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So he continued with the railways until his death or until his retirement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Until his retirement.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Never out of work - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Have you any idea how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Possibly twenty-five or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Berkshire - near Newbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she work before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1060851 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, she was in service in Guildford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1060851 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she do any part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How many rooms were there in the house in Walnut Tree Close?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Could you describe the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, it was one of a group of four - a terrace of four houses - er - there was a front door that led straight into what we called the sitting room and to get into the back of the house you had to go up a passage
way - two houses away - go round and down the back garden. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You couldn't get through to the back of the house from the front?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not from the front - no. - without going round - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So you would have a sitting room and a kitchen downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's right - yes. And - er - well, well I was a bit wrong about the ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How many bedrooms would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 There were three bedrooms - I was wrong. There was a scullery, kitchen or whatever - living room and sitting room. Yes. A six
 roomed house - I'm awfully sorry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did anyone else besides your parents and sister live in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No other relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 One lodger for a short time only - just for a matter of convenience - for him - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But not as a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 At home - all of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 My mother a great mender - yes. My father - nothing manual like that - no - shoe mending or anything - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would your clothes be bought or would they be made by somebody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Bought - ready made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And this would be in Guildford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 In Guildford - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would they always be new or would they sometimes be second hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - always new - so far as I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - bought - oh yes, yes. Yes. Repaired - taken along to what we called the snob - I don't know why i
t was called that but the shoe menders were called snobs in those days - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would there be any special occasion when new clothes would be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No particular special occasion - generally about every year and yougrew up of course and you grew out of clothes - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So they were bought when they were needed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Needed - that's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Very little. He did a very tiny bit of gardening only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he ever do any cleaning or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No cooking - certainly not - no - he was not that sort of chap at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Very little. My mother was a bit bossy and she wanted to do it all her way. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he do the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Getting in coal only. But he wasn't allowed to light the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. No. painting or anything. He was no good at that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So would any painting be done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, a little - er it had to be paid - well the landlord
 did quite a bit when it was really necessary. And I've seen my mother have a go at it too. Yes. And I was allowed to when I got a bit bigger. Yes. Yes, a little - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That was done by the landlord. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Improvements too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, improvements took place while I was there - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your father ever dress or undress or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't think so, I've no recollection of anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he ever tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 He wasn't that sort somehow - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, Walnut Tree Close led down to meadows in those days and we used to go for walks round
 through the meadows only and along by the river - the river was a great attraction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would that be all the way along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - down towards the Woodbridge Road bridge now - in those days there were three sets of meadows in those days
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 The timber?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - not really - I suppose he must have done but I can't recollect any special occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Y
es. A Saturday morning stunt. Er - I had to clean the knives on a board with Wellington knife powder and my sister had to clean the spoons and forks and that kind of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you do any shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, I was sent to the shop with a note, in my early days, to get meat and things like that - yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you continue to do these taks after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - yes, a bit - but not much - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And your sister would have her own tasks to do would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, this - er - spoons and forks as we called them and things like that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And did she continue to help in that way after she left school too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - oh yes, she did a bit - yes, yes. But not a great deal - my mother was a great - what you might call - boss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have to help your sister with things she found difficult when she was young such as dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no. Can't remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you look after her in any other way that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. When we were very young perhaps I did a little but not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she ever help you in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't think so - except that we - in play - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, it was pretty strict - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When was that - would you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Ah - it varied a bit - it was earlier in the winter and later in the summer - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Mother - when I was small - yes - up 'til - well - about ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How old would you be when you put yourself to bed - have you any idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I suppose six or seven - something like that. But that's a guess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - with my sister for a very little while I remember but soon after that - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have a room to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Your parents would have one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's right. They had the room in the middle of the house. I had the front room and my sister had a rather small room at the back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Which room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, there was no bathroom. We had to bath in the - the living room really in one of those sort of baths that we put in front of the fire when it was cold wea-zinc baths - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, sort of - I think once a week - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would this be a special bath night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think it was Saturdays - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Then - after that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 In this living room - yes next - between the kitchen and the sitting room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - no, no, I think not, no, no. Always to that room for a meal - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where would your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And what would she cook with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, in the earliest days she had to cook - in the living room there was a range - a coal range, you know, what I mean - she had to cook on that. But sometimes - I can't tell you
 when - a gas stove appeared - which was a great occasion - yes - yes. And that was in the kitchen you see. Er - scullery I mean - sorry - yes, yes. That made a great difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - I should say eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And what members of the family would be present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, sometimes not my father because sometimes he was not up. If he'd worked very late - as he did sometimes 'til after midnight he had his breakfast a little later. But otherwise we breakfasted - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would he ever go out before you had your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - sometimes - I think some of his turns of duty started at six o'clock in the morning so he had to go out and he came home to breakfast perhaps at nine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So he'd come back for breakfast then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast - can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, one of my recollections is porridge. All my life I've been a porridge friend and - er - I've had it all the time - we still have it and my wife and daughter now have it because I say you must - yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What would you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Tea. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you have a cooked breakfast or would it be bread and butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Bread and butter and - after the - frequently the
re was a little fish I remember - I think haddock was a great favourite - always on Sundays mornings there was a haddock I remember. Sunday breakfast - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have anything different on Sundays for dinner say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, yes, there was more of a cook up on that day from other days - a joint or something like that, you see, and - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about tea on Sunday - would that be a special meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 A slightly special - there was a bit of more cake and things like that but it was ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was it a home made cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
My mother was a great home made - the only thing about it I remember was that if she found you liked a cake you had that for months. Yes. You had not to enthuse about it too much otherwise you'd have it for keeps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 She kept on making the same one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - that's it - yes, yes. There was a concoction called cakeoma which appeared - and we said we liked that and we had that for months - yes - just the same cake - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What would a mid-day meal on an ordinary day be like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, a main meal - yes. It was cold meat and sometimes a stew, you know, she was very good at stews and that kind of thing - yes, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And vegetable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Potatoes and cabbage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And a pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Pudding - yes. Suet puddings you know, the substantial ones - yes. Apple pudding was a great favourite. Oh yes. It still is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 It was just tea. Tea - yes. And for supper - cocoa was in fashion in those days - we had cocoa and bread and cheese 
and - er - lettuce if there was any at the time you know - yes. And things - and apple too - always were a great believer in an apple you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 An apple for supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Cocoa, cheese and an apple?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Apple - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. Quite a bit - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No bottling fruit went on in those days so far as I recollect - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - one particular lot. I remember shallots being done - yes - and making these big - rather big bottles of, you know, sort of shallots - small onions aren't they. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about home made wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Any home made medicines - herbal remedies?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, yes. There was - er - well I don't know whether you'd call it home made but we had to have brimstone and treacle in the spring - yes, yes. I remember that, it was to clear your face, you see. And she was very fond t
oo of getting stinging nettles and making nettle tea - in the summer when it was very hot weather - it was supposed to cool the blood, so we were told - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. Well, I'm wrong about that - no alcoholic 
beer but there used to be a beer called Mason Herb beer I think - they used to make that and bottle it you see so you could have some of that during the summer time but - it was not bad but not exciting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not at - no fruit - no - a little - potatoes and runner beans and carrots turned up occasionally - they were easy to grow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But they would have to buy some?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - pineapple was a great thing to have out of tins in those days - yes. I can't recollect peaches and things like that but I do know that pineapple turned up very frequently in the summer time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You don't remember any tinned or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they keep any livestock for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Yes. My mother had a little place at the back there where she kept a few hens. So we kept ourselves some part of the year with eggs - yes - and the poor creatures had to be eaten some time later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Who would look after the hens - your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Mother - entirely - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think we had meat every day for a midday meal - o
f a sort - yes - I can't remember what - I'll tell you what too - corned beef used to turn up too sometimes. You know, you used to get bigger tins than you see nowadays - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And that would be out of a tin of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not from poaching - no. Now you mention rabbit - we used to buy a rabbit now and again to - er - have - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember seeing your mother have less food so that the family could have more?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I rather think that did happen - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your father have a larger helping than the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - I don't think so because my mother, as I say was bossy, and she said the children must be looked after, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, yes. Yes, no great sort of - well - embargo against talking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think eat a bit of everything was what's good for you - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, it was very - wicked to waste. Yes. And you .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So that wouldn't be looked on at all favourably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no, you to - do your best - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no, I would ask for it - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. I was rather good at that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think so - I think my mother was a bit keen on doing things fairly decently and properly - yes. More or less as I hold them now I t
hink - yes I believe so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, table manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And your sister too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 The same - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not to the table - no. You had to ask to get down too - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And when could you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, when you were finished really and quite near their finishing time too - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So you couldn't get down very early on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not very early on - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Even for the other meals of the day apart from breakfast - your father would be there would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Not always because of his irregular hours - yes. He would have quite a number - of meals left - you know - before or after - generally after us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Fitting in with his ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 His duty times - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you always sit at the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, we had our set places definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And how was the meal served - by whom was it served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Mother - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What order were you served in - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't think father got the first helping - I should think maybe my sister and myself - yes, I think so - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where did your sister sit before she could feed herself and who would feed her - have you any idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, I remember a little high chari you know where she had something - a little table thing in front of her - mother would help her but I never did and I don't think father ever did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would that be while the rest of you were having your meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think so - yes. It was put up close to the table - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Fairly easy, but not entirely easy - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she show affection to her children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not very demonstrative - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 She was not a very easy one to take a secret to or anything like that - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about your father - was he easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh quite easy but no great amount of - er - what I might call common sense somehow. Yes. A bit shallow - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he show affection to you and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh I think so but not with great demonstration - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about your father - could you share any worries you had with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not so much as with mother - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think we were expected to respect them - yes, definitely - oh yes, quite so - yes. Take no liberties - no, but to behave yourself - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And would obedience come into this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your sister in certain ways?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I can't remember any definite sort of instruction or guidance it seemed to come naturally to sort of - er - treat her as - well, a girl - 
you know, to be looked after a bit and all that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 To look after her and would you be expected to be considerate and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And behave properly with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. Oh yes, yes. And not to quarrel. Not to take her toys and things like this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think so - I think I have been told to do that - to look after myself and not to give in - yes, yes. Stand up for yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you and your sister would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I should say - is it easy to say - a bit like them - yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would they bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Er - I might 
tell you - perhaps this will be interesting - my mother and father were amongst the earliest members of the Salvation Army in Guildford - yes. Both were you see - yes. So there was a good deal of - er - guidance in the right direction, as you might call i
t, going on but still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would they think discipline was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Definitely - yes. I've always thought so - always myself - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh - out. Not only swearing but - as I say - Salvation Army was 
narrow you see and I was not allowed to play football when I was - early on - no - not 'til I went to the Grammar School in 1903 - and then that was part of the carriculum really and you had to and my mother didn't take that very easily but football was l
ooked upon by members of the Salvation Army as being a little bit out, you know, its extraordinary - rough and - well the people who sort of took part in it and the danger of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 At mixing up with people who weren't in the Salvation Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, that's right. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - a little - if it was for benefit, you see, but - strangers in the house you keep quiet. Yes. Be seen and not heard - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well - I wasn't afraid of anything happening with my father, you see, he was not that sort of - er - chap - but mother - she had a cane - yes. And I had that a few times in the early days - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What sort of things would you have it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - staying out late at the - in the evening when I was supposed to be home at a certain time - I was playing in the road or somewhere down in the meadows and things like that and - not doing her shopping quite so wel
l as I ought to have done and things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would this happen often?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not terribly often - no. I was a bit - er - not coward but I sort of behaved myself so far as I could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would she came you on the hand or on your behind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, it was not so much on my behind as across my back if I remember rightly. Yes, a nice hefty cane whack you see but .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did it hurt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 A bit - but I could dodge farily easily you see. But the idea of having it that was the disgraceful thing about it I thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What - humiliating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was it ever given you by your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh never - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. Never - no. Easy going he was really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember how you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Resentful and ashamed. Yes, I'm sure of that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Mother - definitely much more important - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
A little different. There would be a little present - but not a great deal because there wasn't much money - yes. But there would be something - yes - for tea - cakes, something a little better, you know, iced cake, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And who would give you presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Mother and father between them. And I can't remember - perhaps an aunt and uncle now and again but not much in that way - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 None outside the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no, definitely not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have any friends in to eat this special cake you might have on your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - occasionally - later on when we were sort of well past ten to twelve and things like that - vary - other nippers
 would come in you see - children from round about. Just a few - two or three - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Except - I can't remember much except - well there were books to read -
 generally a lot of books turned - a number of books turned up and toys to do and - father used to come in and sit with us by the fire and talk and things like that - but mother seemed to have so much to do out in the kitchen all the time, it wasn't until
 very late on Christmas Day for instance that she found herself free to come in and sit and talk to you - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You would have a special meal I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh - in mid-day - yes. With a Christmas pudding and everything - and the things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you go to church in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not then - Salvation Army people, you see. Not church, but we used to go to a service - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Then in the evening would you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. There were very simple games - I think ludo and helmer were great favourites really - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was there a musical instrument in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, you see my father was a bandsman in the Salvation Army - yes. And he was a cornet player - and a most excellent cornet player too. And he'd blast your head off sometimes when - yes - but he was a great cornet player, really good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he practice at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, yes. I don't know what all the neighbours thought of it but they had to put up with it - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Not really - except that later on - let me see - when I was about - er - possibly thirteen or something - I was in this bands as well you see, yes. In fact, I became the deputy bandmaster but that was a bit - it's difficult to remember - I
 suppose I was sixteen or seventeen perhaps, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
I played the euphonium. Made a fair shot at it too. As a matter of fact we had a very fine band here - oh a very good band - yes. You see, in those days we'd no radio - bra
ss bands were it - you see - and they had - it was a bit of a chore you know if you belonged to a Salvation Army band you had three open air meetings on Sunday - oh yes, morning, afternoon and evening and the evening meeting was a great occasion. The open
 
air meeting in the evening was always in North Street opposite - outside the old police station, at the top of North Street. And, as I say, there were no - there was no radio in those days and the people used to turn up there literally in hundreds - oh tr
emendous open air meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And this would be all the year round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
All the year round - yes. It was very seldom that they didn't have one. If it was terrible weather - but generally speaking if it rained you were there, but whenever it was fine th
e crowds were enormous. And - that took place from a quarter to six to about twenty past six and - just about twenty-five past six you formed up in the street went down Wall Street up Market Street down High Street, Friary Street and along to their Citade
l which was - we call it Laundry Road now}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512134\charrsid6631206  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
along there - near enough. And that march was followed by hundreds of people. And at the top of Market Street as you turned into High Street there was always a literal - a great crowd - always to see it - yes. And t
hat crowd came down - there was another crowd at the bottom when you turned into Friary Street - and quite a smaller crowd when you got to the hall. And it was their great sorrow that the people would not come inside to hear the service afterwards. You se
e, they - at the Citadel, that's right. Very few of that big crowd came inside. But the band, as I say, was well worth listening to - it was a very good band - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. No. My mother did a little but she was no singer really - not with any talent - no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I can't say that they did. I think we dragged them into this ludo sometimes, but neither of them was very keen on things like that - no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So this would be your sister and you and perhaps some friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Sister and myself - yes. Anybody who happened to be in there - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever have games out of doors with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I don't think so. We used to have walks - the walk 
to St Martha's was a great thing on Good Friday for instance and things like that you see - yes. You walked a long way in those days without knowing it you see - these days you don't walk - you go in cars but you walked miles then without feeling it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. But they were goodie books you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What - religious books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 More or less - yes. I remember I had quite a number of prizes which were on the goodie side too - the Pilgrims Progress in a mod - in a chi
ldish version and things like that and From Log Cabin to White House was one of the - a very great favourtite President Garfield of the United States - his life from beginning to end and books of that........
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was that a favourite prize?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's r
ight yes. And Christies Old Organ was another old book that was - a bit of a favourtie - yes. I can't tell you much about the story but it was one of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Now, I can't remember - but I think it was the Daily News - er - 
I think, which later on was - linked up with the Daily Chronical I think - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would that come every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not every day - no. As a matter of fact my father would frequently bring one home from the station - but don't ask me how he got hold of it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Perhaps left in the train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Something like that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would there be any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Salvation Army magazines - oh, wait a moment - I'd forgotten - we had the Sunday Companion and the Sunday Circle. If they were reckoned to be all right to be read - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And were they published on Sundays or another day of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Another day - which - it may have been Wednesday or so and kept - and - yes that's right. There were nice little serial stories for children in each of them - 
yes - as well as the olders - Jospeh K Hocking was one of the great writers in those days for the - adult serials, you see - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. There again they were unusual. My father's mother was one of the very
 oldest members of the Salvation Army in Guildford and she lived along in Bavington Place, which was next door to what we used to call the board school, in Sydenham Road. Well, when she died - the Salvation Army made a great do, you see, they had the band
 to lead the procession which went in slow time right from there right right up the Mount to the old cemetery - oh yes. And the police - oh yes, and the police would sort of - shepherd the procession in the town - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would that include the funeral courtege?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes, yes. Everything was there. The Salvation Army band led it you see - right down the High Street. As a matter of fact - to make it a little better - better, I say - they went along and down to the top where the Odeon is now and down th
e full length of Spittle Street as it was then - that's the top of High Street was called Spittle Street in those days and right - it was narrower then - and right the way down the town and I remember too that for her funeral the band didn't stop playing 
the whole time 'til they got to the cemetery gates. Up that terrible hill - the Mount - they kept - oh yes, that went on - the band played the whole way - without a stop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And who would attend the funeral itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 A lot of the Salvation Army people - a tremendous number and a few relatives of my father and mother - I think people like that - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And would people wear special clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, the Salvation Army contingent were all in uniform you see - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And would that apply to most of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - yes - except that other people wore black all the time you know - for any - thing like that. They all went into black. Oh yes - it was a great thing in those days - you had to have something black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How old would you be when this happened? Would you be in the Salvation Army then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. I was a boy at Troothies School then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you be in uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, not in uniform - no - just a boy with the sort of knickers and things like that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So would you have to wear special clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
So far as I recollect the only special thing I had was one of these black sort of little - we called them alpine hats - I think they were called Anthony Eden hats - later on - yes. I had to wear that for quite a time - yes. Very respectable looking.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And would your sister go to this funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh - yes, she went. And she would have something - possibly black ribbons about on her somewhere - things like that - they wouldn't be able to afford black suit or anything like that - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Not a great deal about here but we used to go to my mother's people down in Berkshire every year for a summer holiday. That was a summer holiday always - down in the country there - a country village near Newbury - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you taken shopping sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Yes, particularly at Christmas time. The town was a sight in those days - oh yes - the - the butchers for instance used to load the meat from top to bottom use
d to be all displayed - all these carcasses there and flaring oil lamps hung near them and that kind of thing. In market Street - where MacFisheries is now there was a fishmonger named Phillips and his shop was a sight. He used to be filled with turkeys a
nd chicken and all sorts of things illuminated with oil flaring lights from top to bottom and it was really a sight. You always had to go and see the Christmas shops - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So this was quite an occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh, it was an occasion - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you be taken shopping at other times as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not a great deal - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 If you did go shopping who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Mother - yes, mother was the shopper - if it was a question of a suit or something like that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - not much. As I say, I used to go down into these fields - meadows and that kind of thing and kick a ball about and things like that. Not football mind you. That was different from playing football - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Apart from this holiday - and also on Good Friday you went to St Martha's - did you - do you remember any other cutings that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, my father - in those days they were very mingey with holidays on the railway. He had three days with a free pass - yes t
hree days holiday with a free pass and my mother used to chip him very much and - because he always said Bournemouth, Ryde and Waterlool. You see, we always had a day in Bournemouth and a day at Ryde and a day to London to have a look round a bit there - 
yes, yes. Well, those were the ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 The main expeditions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about Bank Holidays - those were not included?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - no, he sometimes worked and sometimes not. But certain of the Bank holidays - the Salvation Army l
ooked after those. They had visitors from neighbouring corps as they call their - pledgedists.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And you had a special do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, very much so, they Godlaming people would come across and have a big tea for instance in the hall. That kind of thin
g went on - yes. Then you'd have a musical festival at night with the - the other band and yours and - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever go away for another holiday in addition to the one in Berkshire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Only with these - with my father - that's the only ones - were those three days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Just day outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, yes. A day out yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And how long would you go to Berkshire for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I used to go sometimes for a whole month - the whole time that I was away from school. But my mother used to come 
down with the sister for a fortnight. But I was sent on by myself and I used to play with all the local boys down there and go out in the fields helping, mind you, pretending to help with the farm work you see, riding barebacked the horses that were - the
n took them to water and things like that. Oh it was great - yes. I couldn't always sit down very comfortably afterwards.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So you would help on the farm generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Generally speaking - yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 This would be your maternal grandparents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
That's right. And - other relatives - or one or two uncles and aunts down there Used to go out into the fields - they used to do the reaping by hand then and you had to draw bonds for them you see - that means getting a certain number of - lengt
hs of straw and ears you see - that means getting a certain number of - lengths of straw and ears you see and bind them together so they - when they got enough cut up you could bind it round and make a sheaf - yes. There was no stringin in those days with
 - like there is with the binders - yes. So .......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So you really made the binding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
That's right. You - you got a number of straws you see - I don't know - perhaps a dozen or something like that and link them together at the cars so that it was f
airly long and - they bound them then round a sheaf of corn - that's a sheaf of corn you see - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Can you remember how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 There was this work to do in the morning - the knife cleaning and things like that. Yes, 
and sent for the shops - yes. But the afternoon as far as I recollect it was a bit free - quite free.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You could do as you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, more or less - yes. Play with the boy next door and things like that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And then of course Saturday night was bath night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's right - yes. Not too free of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Salvation Army all day. All day. Three times - morning, afternoon and evening - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember what you felt about that - did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
I didn't mind - oh I was delighted because we had - plenty of children in those days - all fam - the people had children, you see, and you had your Sunday school lots of them - yes, yes. But after your Sunday school, for instance, in the afternoon y
ou had to join in the afternoon meeting as they called it you see, so that it was a long session you see. The Sunday school would be from two to three but the open air with the seniors took place from two 'til three nearly and they came back at three then
 they had a meeting inside and you had to go and join in that and stick it out you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And then you had to go on again at six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Six. Although that didn't apply so much until I was in the band you see - no. You used to have to go to the mid - the 
meeting inside which would be about six-forty - inside and stick it 'til eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 It was quite a busy day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. It ended up with a great prayer meeting too, you know, so that it was - it was a - morning 'til night - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And you had different clothes on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, yes. I think we always had a Sunday suit I - set of clothes - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever play games on Sundays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't think so - I think it was looked upon as not being quite right somehow - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would the same attitude be held about working on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
I don't think there was much to be done on Sunday - everything had to be done Saturday if you could do it you see. I think potato peeling and things like that went on on Sunday - yes - that was all
 right, but you couldn't do any other - cleaning and things - and chores and that - had to do it on Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So you think your parents thought it wrong to work or play on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 They would think that yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did both your parents go to the Salvation Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And would they go every Sunday regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Yes, apart from illness or extremely bad weather - as regards mother and the children, but father would go always - whatever the weather, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would there be any special Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes. In those days they were not terribly exciting you see. We had the river here and every year we had a Sunday school outing to Sutton Park or some-where like that in the barge - one of those big barges. They had 
that drawn by a horse - a most gentle sort of trip along the river and getting out there and having a tea in the - on the grass in Sutton Park - that was the Sunday school treat - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And the barge would be hired by the Salvation Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, 
yes, yes. And - they used to sing on the way back you know - it was quite a jolly occasion you see - making all this noise coming along the river.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What would they sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, what they knew from the Salvation Army - yes. I - I think occasionally
 we used to try and sing some of the songs we'd heard of you know - Dolly Gray and things - I can't remember what - but - the - one or two songs that were - in vogue at that time and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Secular songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's right - yes, yes, mm. Goodbye Dol
ly, I must leave you was one you see. I well remembered that - that was from the South Africa war time - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about social activities organised by the Salvation Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, we had - in the non-conformist and other churches they had wha
t they called the Band of Hope - the Salvation Army had to be a bit different - they called theirs the Band of Love, you see, but it was very similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Can you tell me what you did in the Band of Love?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, there were several things. A little bi
t of hand working you see. Fret-work was one of the great things and I happened to be one of the better ones in - you see - used to make brackets and things and little - corner brackets and fitments of that sort which - yes - sold at their sales of work y
ou see, later on-yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh, it wasn't yours - it was given back to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. Actually some were ours - yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And what else did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, they were very keen on - drills with flags and hoops and things like that with one or two m
embers of the band coming in and keeping you - giving you the time you see. Musical drill - yes. Oh yes. I remember those - they were very good too - with barbells, hoops and flags - yes. Oh yes, yes, quite good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they have a choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, they did later on. Let me see now - um -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
No, I was not much of a singer - no - I was in the band you see, but - they had what they called songsters. You see, they had to be different - yes. And they called them of all things - they called them songster brigades, you see, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did the Salvation Army run any temperance club apart from the Band of Love?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not really - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you belong to any other club organised by the Salvation Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - Su
nday schools - yes. The Band of Love which was the - and the bands - yes yes. I shouldn't have - I meant to tell you that my first essay in the band I played the triangle - oh yes, ding, ding, ding - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have any other treats with the Band of Love or the band?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I can't remember - occasionally we'd go for a walk. I remember going up the Green Road as we cal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512134\charrsid6631206 led it - that is past the cemete}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 ry along the top - the Hog's Back. In those days that was a beautiful green road with grass - from bank
 to bank you see - not how it is - oh yes, and that was a good place to go and play and that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You didn't have any evening classes in connection with the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I remember - perhaps when I was twelve or thirteen years of age - I had to 
have a Bible class do you know - oh yes. I was never very good at - wanting to go to things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. We all had to say ours - each of us. Not - my sister and myself - not the parents. We did it for them you see - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not family prayers - no, no. They were not like that somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Not very deep seated but he was a great Liberal - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Why do you think he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I don't know - it was an easy way in those days I think somehow. Er - I can't think why but he certainly was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't think she had any deep sort of feelings about it. No womans votes in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would her views be similar to his do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think so - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember your father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. The great one was 1906 - when the Liberals swept in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And he would vote Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes. That was a great occasion I can remember very much there. It was - the election results when they came in were shown in two places in Guildford. The Surre
y Advertiser offices in Market Street - Conservative. The Surry Times down the - near the buststation - the Friary - Liberals. And we used to go there every night during the com - the election results came in over about a fortnight - oh yes, and we used t
o
 go there every night - the Conservative crowd in - Market Street and the Liberal crowd in - Onslow Street. Used to sit there 'til well after midnight - yes. Results come in - yes. Oh it was very exciting. And I might tell you too that my grandfather - th
a
t's my fathers father - he was a great man for politics - he was a Liberal too - fierce - but he loved to stand in Market Street and harangue the crowd - he talked to them excitedly about the - the hungry forties or whatever he called them, you see, and a
l
l the things he remembered, he said protection no good, you know - that kind of thing and he had to be moved on by police on one - one or two occasions I remember he was - a disturbance and blockage - blocking the traffic you see, oh yes, yes. They took t
heir politics very serious those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you think your father ever felt under this pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. Nothing - nothing - nothing like that - no, no, can't remember any suggestion of that sort - no, definitely not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you know if your father was a member of the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't think so - I'm sure there wasn't. I don't remember him being members of either party in those days like you can be now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he work for the Liberal party at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And your mother wouldn't either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Occasionally my father would take me along to a big meeting, you see, you had meetings in those days - the borough hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Even if there wasn't an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. At the drill hall - I remember going to a marvellous meeting in the 
drill hall once when Mr Holdaine spoke. Oh it was jolly good - very good - and I went to another - actually it was just before the 1906 election - Sir Rupert Isaacs - as he was then - Lord Reading - he was then Mr Rufus Isaacs - he came and spoke in a ter
r
ific marquee on the sports ground - yes. And I remember how convincing he was - you could see that what he was saying was right, you see, all the Liberal ideas - free trade and all the rest - was right, you couldn't help it - he was so - well he - he conv
inced you anyway. I can remember to this day the - how he - wonderful personality - how he made you think that what he was saying was \{ILLEGIBLE\} Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, my mother would sort of bustle about the house making jobs I think you know, mending and things of that sort - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, he was a great chap to sit down and look at a newspaper and have a little doze, you see. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he go out to the Salvation Army at all during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes. There was a band practice on a - may have been a Thursday night - yes. And occasionally a - a mid week meeting of a sort when part of the band would go - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would your mother go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Occasionally - yes. They had what they called a home league - yes and that would - the mothers went along to that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your mother have any interests outside the house apart from this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't think so - not a great deal - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Not very much - apart from these walks I told you about. She was very keen on a nice walk - St Martha's was the one that she loved best of all - walking up through the chantries - through the sand hills up to St Martha'
s. That pleased them no end. She liked the country - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 She'd walk both ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 It varied according to his turn of duty, you see. Sometimes he worked all the evening to midnight - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How many evenings a week would he spend at home when he was not working at his job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, just when he wasn't going along to the Salvation Army really. The ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 They hadn't any other interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I don't think so - no, no, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 He didn't attend any other clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, he was not that sort - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, oh no, definitely not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. Not at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he ever go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did he ever bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't remember much in that day except that the Salvation Army ran a little concern they called the Reliance Bank - you had a little 
box and a little go - used to go into that. That was the only savings I remember. And I don't know how much it ever amounted to but that was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And what would it be used for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's for themselves, you know, I mean for - for clothing and things like that perhaps when they were necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So you don't know if they belonged to any club that would provide some money in the event of sickness or funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 A sick club. A slate club - yes. There was one - I can't think now - used to be co
nnected with the railway there - somebody there used to run a slate club and I can't tell you exactly how - who did it but .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You thought your father contributed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, yes. That meant a little at Christmas or you had the money out just a fortnight before Christmas - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Nor a sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Except a slate club would pay out a certain amount of sick pay - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did you get on with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512134\charrsid6631206 Quarrel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 ed a good deal - yes. Yes, but not too badly - no damage done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you feel close to her in spite of this or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not terribly - no, she was quite different from myself really I think - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Her a little but generally there were some boys in - in the next houses, you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, neighbours children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You used to have to play in the road a bit but generally you cleared off down to the meadows which fortunately were v
ery near to us you see. A matter of - a hundred and fifty yards or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you play in your garden at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Just a little - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Or in the gardens of your friends homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Occasionally - yes, just a little - yes. But you weren't allowe
d - encouraged in that way because - it was dangerous to throw balls - you might break windows you see so you had to go off somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about playing indoors - would you play in your home with a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Occasionally - yes. We'd exchange a little bit sometimes - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What games did you play - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - there was this wretched ludo business and things of that sort and snap was another one you know with cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What would play outside - you'd play with a ball?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Ball - yes, and a little bow and arrow business but that was looked upon as not too good - yes - not too good because - danger - yes, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. They realized you couldn't play without getting 
a little dirty, I'm sure of that, yes. There was always that cleaning up when you went in you see - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember any contrast made with any other children who got dirtier than you or you got dirtier than they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I can't say I remember any comparisons - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not quite - no. They had to be more or less approved. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Certain people - quite definitely. I remember one or two oddments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 They were rather - grubby perhaps and perhaps they swore a bit you see and things like that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So your parents would think that this would be a bad influence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 A bad influence - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have any hobbies when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - not much - but I did a lot of this fretwork that I told you - I gave brackets and things away to all sorts of people you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And this was all done at the ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Done at home, you see - oh yes, I had my own little thing that I attached to one of the kitchen tables you see and used to do my cutting and that kind of thing - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - not much - I remember a jackdaw for a time but so
mehow it didn't last long. And once or twice there was a rabbit but we never liked that very much - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Cigarette cards - yes. And - during the South African war we had buttons with the Generals picture on - little 
- with a pin you stick in your - there - that's right - General Bruder - General Poh Karu and .......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Takings sides with certain .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's right - the best Generals you thought of - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you do any gardening?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I had to do a li
ttle - I don't say I had to but I rather liked doing a little digging in that back garden - yes. I planted a few potatoes now and again and things like that. And did a bit of watering.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I never took much to fishing. Lots of the boys used to fish but I never liked it very much - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But you went for walks you told me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I never had a bike - no. But - when I was twelve or thirteen or fourteen I hired a bike occasionally
 and I did - perhaps at fifteen years of age - cycle from here down to my country place in Berkshire - went - went all that - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So far you've mentioned either walking with your family or the Salvation Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you walk with other companions at different times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Later on - when I was at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512134\charrsid6631206 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 rammar school for instance - a little group of us used to go - when we had our Holidays. We used to go to Cut Mill and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512134\charrsid6631206  places like that - yes, yes. We}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 'd have a day out with a few sandwiches - bread and cheese and things like that to keep you going - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - not really - there was no great sporting while I was at Trinity School but in 1903 when I was at the Grammar school - football and cric
ket came up - see, and you played quite regularly - I got to - school - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you go to any theatres when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. Out. Not ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't remember much concerts except Salvation Army ones - yes. But theatres were looked upon as works of the devil you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about music-halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 The same - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, cinemas came in a bit late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would they be while you were still at school or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't think so. I remember the Regal
 - and what they call the Plaza - that was the first one that opened in Guildford. And that was 19 - well, I remember, 1908 or nine or something - ten perhaps - seeing one or two films there. And also someone brought one along to the Salvation Army once w
hen they were very - new - yes, and showed us a very jerky sort of - picture you see which we thought was wonderful. But I remember - I couldn't say when it was - it might have been 1911 or '12 - at the Plaza the big film that was reckoned to be -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512134\charrsid6631206  it was a big film too - Quo Vai}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512134\charrsid6631206 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 s - I don't know the pronunciation - Quo Vadis and that - that was shown - I remember that - a very good film - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Very little. It was only in coppers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have it regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - almost - but not quite. I used to get a few extras for the lady next door. Tuppence for going as an errand for her and things like that you see. Used to get
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How much would you get from your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Only a few coppers - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, I - I think it was generally sweets but now and again you put a few bits by you know so you had a shilling or two when - put by sometimes - not often - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
No, I don't remember very much, but she was really great the other way - helping other people - oh yes - a good nurse. People who were sick - neighbours and that often sort of - called for her for a bit of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512134\charrsid6631206  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 advice and things like that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Actually, I don't remember that happening? No, she was pretty strong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When your sister was born for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh, I've no idea - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How would she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
I've no idea - I was just about two then and I can't remember anything of that. But - er - neighbours were very good in those places, you know, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. My mother's brothe
r lived two doors away from us in Walnut Tree Close - yes. He was a ticket collector on the Guildford railway - yes - a very fine chappie - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How much did you see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Quite often. Several times a day - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would that be at work or would they visit each other in their homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 They'd go round and talk to each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, a few. There again, I'm sorry about it, but it was generally Salvation Army friends - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And would that be where they saw them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, yes, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - more or less I think - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your mother have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, yes - she had a few of the women at the S.A. who used to do all the te
a making and all that kind of thing you see. Great friends with them - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would they come to see her in her own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not very often. But they had - they did come at times - just occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would your father have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not much - no, no. His work mates as you might call them - but they never came to the house - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were other friends invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 There wasn't a great deal of visiting - no, no, no. Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 If they did, would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think they would if it happened to be near a meal time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would there be any particular day or occasion when they might be invited in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - I can't think of anything - no. it would - it would be just chance meetings anyway - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you say that the friends invited in, when they were, were your mother's friends or your father's friends or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I should think mother's only - almost only - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did friends ever call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think so - but very little, you see there wasn't much visiting between - as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about neighbours - would the same thing apply?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. A little bit over the fence at the back and that kind of thing you see - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And might they come round without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Just a little - oh yes, for some reason or other - yes, but - something or other - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not a great deal - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Pe
ople often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements - what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Nothing very much you know, it would only sort of - I wouldn't say gossip - but something very near t
hat and that's about you know it. - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 They wouldn't have any music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Or games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no, definitely not games - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Many people divide society into different social groups in that time before 1918 did you think of som
e people belonging to one group and some to another? Would you be conscious of this as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 A bit - well - yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How would you describe the different ones? As you saw it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - actually when I - I went to the Grammar school 
you know in 19 - I went to the Grammar school from Holy Trinity school in 1903 and it was then that I realised more than ever before the differences you see. In those days the scholarship boys at the Grammar school were few and far between. In my year the
r
e were two four - five of us only from the whole of Guildford - yes. And the rest were paying you know - er - fees and that kind of - and they looked down a bit on this - unfortunately into the scholarship boys - yes. And - the masters unfortunately were 
just a little bit tinged with that as well, but they soon got over that because the scholarship boys - after all - they learned their job and they soon showed up a bit in school you see so that - they became - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Their work was good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Good - a
nd - they - made the grade as it were, you see, and the differences - but I did realise then that some people had so much more money than we had and better clothing and you know, more means altogether - that's when I first realised - came up against diffe
rences.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
How could you describe those differences - in what sort of group would you think of the boys whose parents could afford to pay fees to send them to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, you - you'd rather - little bit of - sort of - wishing we were a little more
 like them for instance - had a little more money and that kind of thing but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What group would you say that you were in yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, to start with we'd very little spare money and that kind of thing - yes. And it was very difficult for mothe
r and him to let me have enough pocket money to equal the - the pocket money that the other lads of that type had, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How would you describe your own social group? Would you describe that as working class or.....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 More or less - oh yes, I think so, definitely - working class really - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What sort of group would the boys be in if their parents could afford to pay fees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, a lot of them were tradespeoples children - yes. And I remember ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What would you call that group - how would you think of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - well I don't know what to say about that - they were a little bit - proud - middle class - getting on towards it - yes. I remember for instance the - the man who ran the Railway Hotel at Guildford. He had th
ree sons at the Grammar school when I was there and there was Girdlestone down the High Street who had a - a shop, you see, and - well several of the fellows they - they - their people had shops in the High Street and that kind of thing. And they thought 
they were no end of - er - you know, up there sort of thing - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What sort of people belonged to the same social group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, one chappie who went in with me - his father was an engine driver - he went from Stoke school - he was jus
t about the same group as myself really. Two others - well one of them - his father had - his name was May and he had a blacksmiths shop - in the Friary courtyard there - yes. He was that sort of chap you see, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Can you remember any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not a great deal - no - not in detail. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What sort of people belonged to the other groups? For instance the tradespeople you mentioned would be one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Now how would people like teachers and doctors fit into this grouping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I do
n't think we had many children of doctors and teachers there - not that I can recollect - there must have been a few but I just can't recollect them, at all
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you come across them at all out of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not really out of school - no, no. The 
little group that went on walks with me were more or less from my own group, you see - yes, May and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And I suppose in the Salvation Army you would be socially much the same sort of grouping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, that's right - a bit that way. G
enerally working class people as it was then. There were very few people with much money in the Salvation Army - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. We were always told that you would 
be - proper to everybody you see - yes, yes, oh that was - mother was great on that. You'd be polite and just as you should be to everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well - yes. Not a great deal apart from
 school I'm afraid - touching the cap. But you had to do it - bunch your cap up and take it off to all your masters if you saw them - at the Grammar school - oh yes, yes. You had to do that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was there anyone you called Sir or Madam or Master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - I'm a bit that way inclined. I'm inclined to say Sir to people even nowadays if it's somebody - comes to church and - a visiting clergyman and things like that - that's stayed with me. I say Sir to him the first time I speak to him, you see - yes,
 that stuck with me - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Is this because you're showing respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Respect - but no sort of - bobbing down - no. But respect for his rank or status or something like that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not a great deal - no. They didn't inspire that sort of thing - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 In the district who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, the doctors and the clergymen. The clergymen visited a lot more in those days than they do now I believe and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Why do you think they were felt to be important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, a doctor - you had to rely on a doctor for some - and you looked upon him as a man with great knowledge, you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was it a question of education partly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. Really - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I suppose this would apply to the clergymen as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about people with wealth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I think you felt a bit that way to them but I never met many - I didn't - no - not actually.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you come into contact with doctors and clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, not really - no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about the shop keepers - who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I - I think a lot of the shop keepers weren't a great deal better than we were in a way as regards educati
on and that kind of thing - yes. Yes. More money - oh yes - plenty of money lots of them - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about teachers - how would they come into this sort of picture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, you looked up to your teachers in those - I think they were grand peo
ple. They were devoted to their jobs - the - the teachers that we had at Holy Trinity school. I remember today how devoted they were and how good they were - yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you know any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Only in slight way by going for those holidays in Berkshire - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And how would they be regarded?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, we looked up to them a bit you know - yes. But they weren't so much as their own farmers - they were sort of bailiffs - there was a great landlord in those days - lived at Wantage - had 
all round about and they rented farms from him you see. Tenant farmers - that's the word - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about employers - did you come across them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No - not really - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, a tremendous number of people used to go to church - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And would they be a certain class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - I think a mixed class really - quite definitely - yes. Some of our neighbours for instance went to St Nicholas very regularly - they were just about the same as we were and - I say St Nicholas because that was Walnut Tree Close you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That would be the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's right - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would there be more wealthy people at St Nicholas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh very much so - it was looked upon as being 
quite a wealthy church - yes. For instance, when the Salvation Army had their self denial week which took place in Lent, more or less, you see, they never called it Lent, but my mother used to go the clergy were very good - they used to let - a member of 
t
he Salvation Army stand outside one Sunday morning and - with the box. No shaking it - and just stand there mute you see and my mother always used to go to St Nicholas church and she said how nicely she was treated there by everybody and practically every
body dropped something in her box. Yes, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about the chapel - what sort of people went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, they were a mixture too you see - yes. A lot of the - what do you call it - the shopkeepers of Guildford were chapel people. Mr
 Gammon for instance who ran the Grocery store. I'm not sure but I think he was Congregational I think so - yes. And there were others who went to the Weslyeian - they were the great - they called them Wesleyians in those days - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And they would be shopkeepers - would there we working class people as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, yes - that was right away through the .......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But would there be as many in the upper group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 In the chapels? I think more in the church - yes - the churches - yes - kind - little bit -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about Roman Catholics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I never came in contact with any when I was a boy. Not that I remember - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 There was no friction with Roman Catholics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no. No, never heard of anything - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think different groups in so far as some mothers like mine was very, very good at - from an economy point of view - make the most of
 what she had. Others were not so good - they never had a penny to spare, you see what I mean, they wasted it yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would they then have a slightly lower standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 They would so - quite definitely - yes, yes. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And how would this show - in their clothes and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
A bit in their clothes - yes. And you - if you called there for the boy to go to school you see, you'd see that the breakfast there was a little bit - not quite so nice as yours was. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, I think there was quite a bit of that - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were some families though of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, yes, we used to talk of people like that - my mother did - yes. They were rough and .......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would this distinction be made for instance between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't remember much friction or anything arising through that - no. I don't remember anything .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Woul
d the distinction between a family described as rough would they be labourers with no skill and people who were more respectable be more skilled or would this not apply?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think it would be - you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 A bit of each?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's right - yes, yes. A bit of character with - very .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would come into it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So it depended on the personality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Personality of the people. Some people made a lot of - of a little you see. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different groups?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - yes, to a certain extent I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they look at things the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I don't t
hink anything like that worried her or made her - she thought about it really, you know, she just plodded on her own way irrespective and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was it possible at that time to move from one group to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, it was possible but I - I can't think of - I can't think of it happening not with the people I knew - not actually - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, I heard the expression - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And what sort of person would you feel it indicated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, I should think for instance a person who treated everybody in the proper way somehow - they weren't sort of very much influenced by the amount of money you had but - they treated you properly irrespective of what you had or showed, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Treated you as a person, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Person - that's right - yes. There were people like that I'm sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Very little - no - very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Actually - there was more drunken}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 ess in those days but he didn't come near us particularly. But you knew it round the public houses you see. Policemen were always there very busy on Saturdays and Fridays - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your mother say if you were naughty - I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, she might have done and probably did - but - I can't remember 3/8 no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How do you think the policeman treated the people - have you any idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think they were very good really. I ca
n't remember any brutality or any tendency that way - no. No. I think they were quite rough with these drunks as they called them - oh yes, yes. They had to be almost - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Rented - yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. An agent who collected the rent only - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I thought he was a bit of a nuisance. But - just vaguely remember - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Quite definitely. Yes, we knew they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did you think about that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I liked it. Particularly when I went to the Grammar school - I was - a certain strain on them in a way because lots of boys us
ed to go to work at fourteen and so you see, whereas I was a non - sort of starter in that respect you see - I stayed at school 'til I was seventeen. I know that was a bit of a pull for them - yes. And you had - scholarships in those days didn't do everyt
hing - we had to buy quite a lot of books - oh yes - quite a number of books we had to buy. It was fa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206 ir}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
ly expensive too and you had to - sort of toe the line in one or two things like the sports day and the - down at the sports ground. You had to turn up in
 your running shorts and all that kind of thing. Things that we - yes - things that you wouldn't have bought in the ordinary way - yes - small things but somehow they tolled a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Never out of work - no. And he was never ill - he was remarkably - he died at ninety seven so - yes - so - yes - he was never ill to my knowledge 3/8 no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your family ever have to get help from the guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, nothing like that - no. They were were very independent - they wouldn't have asked for anything anyhow - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you given lessons by one of your parents before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. It was a funny thing but - I am pretty h
ealthy and always have been - but I don't know what - why it was but I was a white livered white faced sort of a boy and had to have the doctor called in and he said he must not be taught any-thing yet, you see, and it wasn't until I was six that I was al
l
owed to go to school and then unfortunately I didn't know ever the alphabet you see when I went to Trinity school and they said well, you must go into standard one, you see, and but all the boys there knew their alphabet so I was put in the back row with 
two boys, and I remember their names and they had a book with pictures and the letters and I learnt the alphabet and I soon caught hold of it you see and I caught the others up. But I started school like that - as a boy not knowing anything really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You were six then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Six - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When you first started what time in the morning did you go? And when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 We had to got to school at nine and I think it closed at four - I believe so. And it was a long walk you see - it was a good
 mile from Walnut Tree Close up to - I went to Trinity school by the way because my father went there - yes. He went in Bavington Place in Sydenham Road you see and he went to Trinity school. And they thought that was the best place to send me - so I was 
sent there and I'm glad I did because I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you go home for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - often yes - but in the bad weather no. We used to take some sandwiches and we could cat them in school. That meant no drink - nothing to drink I remember. There was no sort of coffee or anything like that but .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When would morning school finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think twelve - it may be twelve fifteen but I think twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And then afternoon school would start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Start at two. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And that was a church school wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, a Church of England school - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were there girls there as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes. On one side was girls and the other boys - yes. And throughout Lent for instance we used to be marched - real marching, bang, bang, ban
g, to Trinity church, you see - Ash Wednesday and all the following Wednesdays - yes, used to march round and have a service in the church and march back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Walked - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I should think it took me a jolly good twenty minutes or more - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, I started off with two - a man - a boy and a girl who lived opposite to me and happened to be going there so they took me for the first time until I was allowed to go on my own - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I rather liked it. Oh yes, I did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, as I think I said before - I think they were devoted to their job and somehow that i
mpressed me at the time - yes, they were so patient you know. Of course they had a cane you know - oh yes, the canes were - and I had it a few times for something or other - can't tell you what for but - they were good teachers and - on the whole I liked 
school very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they emphasise certain things as important in life - such as manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. There was a good deal of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, quite definitely. They were very good teachers throughout - not only in the curriculum but in manners and mode of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was punctuality important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes. Very much so. In fact now I can think of it - it was - a few of my stripes on the hand was for being late - afternoon school, you see, from Mr Prescot - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 If you did something the teachers disapproved of would you be caned or would there be other punishments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - so much to write many times - quite often. But sometimes for bad things - the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would the girls have the same sort of treatment as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
I don't think it was any corporal punishment - but I - no, no. But writing things over and over again you know that had to be done - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You don't know for what offences the cane would be brought in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well - being cheeky to master was a great one you see - yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Mother did - but father was a bit casual - he - he did a little - yes, but mother was the great one - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. And you must get on you see - you must learn the stuff properly so that you get on - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - no. My mother never went to Trinity school for any p
urpose that I know of - remember. That happened differently at the Grammar school. She used to come to the speech days and at the sports on the - sports day on the sports ground. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would she meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. And say how's he doing, you know, and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But in Holy Trinity she wouldn't have known the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
No, no, I don't think so - no, I don't think she - I think she possibly did see Mr Prescot once or twice, I'm not too sure about that. Yes, headmaster - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did the other children at Holy Trinity school come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh very much so - yes. There were a few exceptions - for instance - in that photograph I showed you was Mr Prescot - the headmaster's boy - he was one of us, you see - yes. He lived in a much better house in Bailey Road and things like that you see - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think there was a bit of favouritism going oh you see - they like
d people who got on well, you know, and gave them a little extra on the quiet - I think - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When you say got on - do you mean with their work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 With their work - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 A bit that way - ye
s. Used to be a little bit - tendency to cruelty almost - to - one or two - yes - but nothing very serious. Because - a little bit of brow - beating going on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would this be boys who tended to bully?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, a bit that way - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Not very much so. The masters used to - or teachers used to come out into the playground and I think they would have sort of - urged anybody standing by to join in games, you see, I'm sure of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You don't remember any child at your first school who seemed to be isolated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I don't remember that - no. I think we - we joined in pretty well. In the playtimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And then you went on from there to the Grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, yes. And that was quite different, you know, really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How old were you when you first went to the Grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Thirteen years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When you first started what time in the morning did you go? And when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 We started at nine o'clock and - I think it was four - it may have been four-fifteen - but probably four in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you stay to lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no, I went .......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And what time would you go home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I rather think it was twelve-fifteen and back at two - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What kind of a school was it - it wasn't a church school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 It was a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 An ancient foundation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. King Edward the sixth ran it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 It would be a private school in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, really - yes. Scholarship places - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And how long did that take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I should think it took twenty minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did anybody go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did you think of the Grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
I was a bit - very impressed first time - oh very much so - yes. Very dignified Headmaster and so on and I'd never, had masters, of course, with gowns - caps and gowns before - that was all new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That impressed you too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh very much - after the first strangeness had gone - yes. And very soon made friends with most of the fellows that I came in contact with.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about the teachers in their gowns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, I though that ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you find them stand offish?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no, I couldn't say any of them was that - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You got on well with the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh quite, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were there any particular ones you didn't feel were so congenial as the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I can't think of anyone who stood out that way - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they emphasise certain things as important in the way that your other teachers had done such as manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. They certainly expected us to have good manners without being taught by them, you see, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about tidiness and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes, that was a great thing - you - I can't think what happened if you were late now - but - you certainly had to be punctual - when the bell rang - there was a few minutes and then it was assembly - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about the way you spoke? Was that important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh I think so. You had to show due respect - yes. I - I can't remember - the manner of speaking I can't remember anything being said particularly - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I suppose some of the boys would have a slightly different accent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - just a bit that way - yes - but not much - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would they be corrected at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - pick it up I suppose - yes I think - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, there was that - wretched business of writing out so many lines quite often you know - yes. I didn't qualify for that too many times - just a few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And what else did they do apart from giving you lines to write out - was there a severer punishment for worse offences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes. I - can't say that it happened much - but you were marched to Mr Honeyborn - the Headmaster and he had a cane - that's the worst that could happen yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And what would that be for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - insolence - oh yes, definitely - yes. And I can't say - any - it wouldn't be for - the lack of any quality in your work or anything - I don't say that - no it would be some bad manners or something of that sort you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Particularly mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - yes, quite a bit - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 My mother used to go - only my mother - she used to come on speech days and sports days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she meet the teachers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you have stayed longer if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I would have done but my parents were rather anxious for me to start earning you know. Yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not immediately - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But you did later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 A little bit - but that's a long time on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I should say that I - I could have gone on I could have done a better thing made a better job - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you think you benefited from the schools you attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Quite definitely - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little extra money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
I had junior clerkship in the Post Office - civil service at Guildford. I was very fortunate - well, I passed the civil service examination you see - and I was quite fortunate - there was only one job of 
the type in Guildford and it fell vacant just when I wanted it so I was lucky - yes - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you apply through the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no. No. No, just filled in this normal civil service application form and sat for their examination - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And the job happened to be vacant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
That's right. It was a job hot only for, you know, it was a job for - most of the jobs were for jobs in London - most of the vacancies - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh well, it w
as a most interesting job. I did - many better things than I did later on - yes. It was a peculiar office - it was in the Post Office Telegraph Engineers office. And the staff was a company quartermaster - by the way I should tell you that the telegraphs 
i
n the south of England were run then by K company of the Royal Engineers - and this job - it was a small office - the - controller or engineer as he was called was a company quartermaster sergeant in the Royal Engineers, K company. And he had two corporal
s
 and a sapper and the boy - yes - and that was the staff. I was the boy - yes. And the area they did - worked for extended Leatherhead, Chertsey, Working, Hazlemere, Basingstoke and all round - Cranleigh and all that - a very big area and it - at that tim
e they were opening telegraphs everywhere - er - telephone circuits all over the place - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What hours did you work - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. I worked from nine 'til five with an hour for lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you work on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Saturdays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Saturday morning - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no, no. That was the half day - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Er - now I'm very sorry - I can't say whether it was a week or a fortnight - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What would you be paid - do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh - it's a shock - a tremendous wage - fifteen shillings a week to start with - yes - with an increment of a shilling ever year. A shilling increment - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you feel that was a fair wage at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3824808\charrsid6631206 Oh wel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 l, I was very pleased to get it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, but I can't tell you how much now - I used to keep just a little pocket money - but not much - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What would she use it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, she put it into the general sort of purse - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would she pay for your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think she did while I was there - yes, yes. I'm sure of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you pay anything for board - that would be taken out of what you gave here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Taken out of what I gave here, you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And you would have a little pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, that's right. It would only be a shilling or two. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh splendidly - excellently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You enjoyed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes. As a matter of fact when I left they gave me a lovely leather kit bag - oh yes, they made a great fuss and I've still got it - all those years ago - it's fine - yes. Oh I got on really well with them. They tried their 
very hardest to keep me there when I passed the second examination.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 The first examination would be what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 It was a boy clerkship - yes. But you had to be out of that by twenty unless you - on the streets if you hadn't passed another exam - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did your immediate employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, very well indeed, because I - as I say I got on awfully well with all of them - yes. I was called sonny and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh well, I looked up to him rather. He was a - a good chap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did you feel about the work - did you enjoy it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes, I did. It's the most amazing variety of work - it - I had to make pay bills - we had - the - the engineer employed about three gangs - construction gangs in various pa
rts of the district and - their wages had to be computed and being civil service you know the rates of pay were something farthings quite often and the overtime rates were time and a quarter and time and a half for certain others and so on, you see, so it
 was quite a little - arith met -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Arithmetical problem?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's right - yes. That was one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you do any part time jobs in addition to this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did you do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 After the - after Post Office? Well, I p
assed this second examination you see, and I started at Somerset House, London in the Inland Revenue department.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And that was through the examination? You applied in the same sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And what did you have to do in that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, it was very dud, I'm sorry to use that work but it was very - like that after this great variety of work that I had there. It was - you're one - doing one kind of work most of the day - card indexes and all that sort of thing - mo
notonous really, it was - yes. Quite a lot of it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What did you have to do - mostly card indexing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
And - that's right - and acknowledging letters and the most exciting job and - and - well, another interesting job was that it was in the estat
e duty office and - the - estate duty was com - was computed by the examiners there but - for instance - people who'd held lots - stocks and shares - it was our job to check the values - of these form the stock exchange - daily stock exchange - what do th
ey call it - the daily - register or whatever - there's a separate one issued every day - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What hours did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, it was better than Guildford in a way. It was ten to five you see - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And you would have Sunday off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes - and Saturday afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That was your half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And did you have holidays with pay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. I believe I'm right to say that it was a fortnights holiday - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And do you remember how much you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes. Wonderful wage. I got - yes - fifty-five pounds a year to start - paid monthly - and of course the first month was a bit boring because it was a long time coming to the end of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Because you had to wait until they made up your money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 They made up my money - yes - that's right. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, in a way - yes - but not entirely - it seemed a bit low because the railway fare was quite expensive - it's much better than now of course - it actually worked out at seven and six a week from Guildford to Waterloo in those days - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you give any of the money then to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You continued to live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Live at home - and - I'm sorry I can't say what I gave her but 
- I kept a little more of course - I had to - because I had to buy lunches there you see - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And presumably you paid for your railway fare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, that came out of it - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you now be buying your own clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think I was - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would your mother put what you gave to her into the general housekeeping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's what happened to it I'm sure. Oh no, not in a separate pocket - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did you get on with the people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I'm one of these fel
lows who - I must be weak minded or something - I seem to get on well with most people you see, and I was - soon make some - quite a lot of good friends - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did your immediate employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh quite well - yes. A little bit of 
brow beating as a start you know, but they soon got to know you weren't too bad I suppose and I got on well - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I can't say that I liked the very first one I had but fortunately in a way I was soon transferre
d to another room and - and I got on much better with that chappie - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, it was a bit boring because it was a block of work you see, you didn't get much variety - it was a bit monotonous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Not really - no, no. Actually of course the hours were not bad you see from ten o'clock 'til five - it's not a very long day somehow with a break of an hour for lunch - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 At what stage did you go into the army - what age did you go into this job in Somerset House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 At twenty - when I left the Post Office at Guildford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 1910. Yes. Yes, 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So you stayed there until .......?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 19 - July 1915. And what happened was the war broke out of course in Au
gust 1914 and - Somerset House happened to be the headquarters of the Civil Service Rifles - 15}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206  Bat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
ion London Regiment - a splendid Regiment and I knew quite a number of people in it and the drill hall was just near in Somerset House and when war brok
e out they were doing their annual training - the battalion - and they were all hauled back to their headquarters - Somerset House - so that then we had them living in the corridors and we had all the smell of the army boots and everything else you see an
d
 we all were mad to join. And any amount of us tried to join and we were told you must stay - it's most important that you should stay here and do the work of national importance so - but you will perhaps be released a little later. Yes. So we were waitin
g and most anxious to join - quite a number of us. In July 1915 - yes - they said - actually a group of eight were allowed to go and we were overjoyed and we all joined the Civil Service Rifles - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When you returned from the war - that would be ......?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 1919. Yes. The armistice was 1918 - well I was in France until 1919 - about - I'm not sure - but I - it was about March or April - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And you went back to Somerset House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. Yes. To the same job. Well, not in the same room but the 
same type of job - although I was very soon moved to another job - much more interesting - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I rather liked that kind of thing - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you say that your early time at Somerset House was a training period or an apprenticeship in any sense?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Not really - no. It was just simply - more or less sim - fairly simple work it seemed to me anyway and it didn't lead anywhere at all - just then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you belong to any professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, I can't say that I've ever even thought much on those lines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you feel there were divisions of interest amongst the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes, you had - yes, you had some who were what are now called sort of - trouble makers you see - yes. I could never get enthusiastic over that - there was not trade union with us then but it was in embryo you see and they were anxious to for
m something - yes, yes. Dissatisfied and - sending memorials to the treasury and telling them how badly we were paid and all that - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But you hadn't much sympathy with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not much - no. I can't say that I had. And I could never bring 
myself to go to their rather boring meetings when they were doing nothing but slating the treasury and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did it achieve anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, it did in the end - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh - I don't know what to say about that. I sort of - er - get a bit more nature as I went on but I - I can't say much about that - no.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 After school you went on living at home until you went in the army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That's right - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no, no, we went on just as before - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about your - brother wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, sister. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did it change your relationship with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no. She wasn't at home a great deal because by the time the war was finished she'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1060851 Married
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206  and living in the North of England and we saw very little of her - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no. I was still in the Salvation Army band.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not Sunday school - you mean after ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When you started work did you continue going to the Band of Love?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I don't think so. I was a little too grown up I thought by that time - let me
 see I was - er - oh when I started work - 1910 wasn't it - yes. Oh - well it's difficult to say when I gave up the sort of young peoples do's and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 During the period when you left school and went into the army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. Yes. Yes, that's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you take an interest in politics at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh yes. Not very seriously but I had very Liberal tendencies because that was ground in when I was young and as it happened the master of Grammar school who taught Economics and that kind of thing - he was a fr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 e-trader to the very back bone you see and - it - that was the only thing I could see that was right - he so convinced us - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You told me earlier something of how you spent your spare time - now you said you discontinued the Band
 of Love - did you continue to do any of the other activities in the same sort of way as before or did you do different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think - there was Mr Pimm who I've mentioned - he had by that time joined the Salvation Army and he was a great man for the you
th and he used to take us out for walks and we used to have a Bible class and - but I can't think of any other things particularly - apart from that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not a great deal - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Who would you go with if you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - well, one of my S.A. friends - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where would you go to? What would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, - you wouldn't believe it but the cinema was barred according to our people and the S.A. You see, they didn't think that was right - you see - they were very narrow minded in those days so there wasn't anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You weren't allowed to go?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not really - no. At least by that time I could - choose myself I suppose, to go but I didn't go - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What else would there be to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Nothing - except go for walks and that kind of thing and go to my friends house and have a game and - something like that but .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What sort of game would you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, there was ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would it be a card game?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, one or two simple card games - I was never one for really difficult card games - I could never put my mind to it I'm afraid. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you make any new friends at this time when you started full time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - just a few - but not much - no - because the people I worked with were grown men - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And did that apply in London as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - well, no - there were lots my own age but we lived in different places, you see, I didn't see - no - because I can't think - I didn't travel from Guildford with any of my colleagues for instance - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you go out with them in London at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, lunchtimes and that kind of thing - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever bring them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, I can't think of anything - no, I didn't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - the only special friend I can remember was one of the people I knew as a boy and they moved away to Portsmouth and took over a confectioners shop and I had quite a number of holidays down there - yes, yes. Stay with t
hem - yes - and my friend had to work in the bake house and I thought it was a glorious thing to help him, you see, yes. And then of course we had everything that Portsmouth had to give in the evenings - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 That must have seemed very good after Guildford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh it was very, very - after Guildford - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about girl friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, I had one or two half-hearted girl - affairs - when I was a boy - but - they never got anywhere and I was not terribly interested - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - well, they knew them because they belonged to the Salvation Army you see, several of them - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But they wouldn't know your London friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no, no. They never met any of those - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did they expect to know where you were if you were out and about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think so - yes - I should say they did - not my father so much - he was a bit - free and easy but mother would be very keen to know - yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you expected to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, but not terribly - not a very strict rule that way - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think you said you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1060851 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206  in 1915?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was that before you went in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No - it was exactly at the same time. Yes, you see it happened like 
this - we had been engaged for some - year or two you see and this war business you see - we thought I don't know if I join the Army could rather be sent off quickly so we got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1060851 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206  straight away to make quite sure you see. But ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So you would then be twenty-five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - yes. Let me see - 1915 - yes twenty-five - yes, yes, twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How long had you known your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well - my wife is my first cousin and I've known her ever since I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 All your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, tha
t's right. And I can't tell you when we got a bit more sort of friendly together and - it must have been 1910 or something like - I can't think you know, quite - but .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Berkshire - near Newbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was this the family you used to go and visit as a boy for holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Yes, I used to go to my grandmother's who was at a little country place called Beadon and my wife lived four miles away over the Downs - there was a bit of going and coming when I was there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So you knew her in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you save up money before getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1060851 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206  or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes. And - I used to be chapped because - they said my bank book had got as many withdrawal entries as it had deposit entries you see 
- but it gradually got a bit more. In total.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your parents help you in setting up a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Only in very sort of little odd ways but actually of course we - we didn't set up home very - soon, because I came out of the army in 19 - 1919 and there was no chance of getting a house then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Where would your wife live after you went in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, she lived partly with my people and partly with her own people in Berkshire. Used to go between the two - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I should think two to three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Could you describe the wedding?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, it was - as I say it was a very rushed affair - because I was going into the army on the - I was sent away from the office - they said in three days time you can joi
n up, you see, so we went along and did that. Well, we had funny ideas - I thought I might be sent right away so I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206 what they called a common licens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 e which enabled us to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1060851 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206  on the third day of - after giving notice you see, so that was a very qu
iet wedding - a wedding at my home in Guildford - no fuss and noth - hardly anything at all - just that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you have any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh just a little bit from the people inside but hardly anybody knew about it, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Just the family you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, that's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And would you have any guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Only just - an uncle and his wife and daughters lived nearby and they were the only people who came in if I remember correctly - yes. That's all - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And you didn't have time for a honeymoon did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Oh no. No, no. No, because almost the next day I went to Somerset House to join and that was that. But I - as it happened the first month in the army was spent on the square at Somerset House - because - Headquarters of t
he - so I used my season ticket - which hadn't run out - to come home to Guildford and lived like that you see for the first month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So you did see a bit of her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh then, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How old was your wife when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1060851 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - let me see - I was - she was twenty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did your wife have a job after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no, no. No she just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she work before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1060851 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. She was in service - she was a parlormaid actually - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But she didn't work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1060851 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she work subsequently at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Never. No, not after marriage, no. We had a - a separation allowance you see, an army one - not very much but it helped a bit and of course I had the balance of pay from t
he Civil Service you see - they took - the army was paid then the magnificent sum of a shilling a day you see so that was taken away from my Civil Service pay - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You had one daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What date would she be born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 1917.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You weren't with your wife when she was born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Er - not really - no. Actually I came home wounded from the Somme in - 1916 - September 1916 - I came home in October - and - I had a long period of convale}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 cence had a knee wound which led to six mo
nths treatment to get my knee working properly again and - all that time my wife came and lived with me - it happened to be at Seaford - there was a very big camp there and actually I got a sleeping out pass and we lived a very - well we thought it was a 
good thing - that's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But then you went back in the army before the baby was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes - by then my leg was all right }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206 and I'd gone back to the reserve}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206  bat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 ion of my Regiment - the 15}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
 London Civil Service Rifles - that was at Win
chester then and it was while I was at Winchester that Joy was born but just before that - because it looked to me as if I would be just on the point of going back to France and I thought well it's a bit awkward if Joy's just coming along so I applied for
 a commission and that was the only reason that I did so - I hadn't any funny ideas as to being - a top-notch or anything like that - and - I got this all right - yes, oh yes, and that kept me England until Joy was a few months old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So that worked quite well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes it did - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Do you know if your wife had any medical help when the baby was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, but not enough, you see - the doctor down there was very cape - very kind but not as capable as he should have done because there was a
 certain amount of repair to be done we found out afterwards which was only superficially done and in
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was this in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Berkshire{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 In Berkshire - the little village - yes. So that led to her being rather - very seriously ill in a few years time and th
at is the basis of all her bad health since - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You don't know how long your wife was in bed do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Er - well, I was in camp at - Winchester - I should think only a week or two - week or so - week or ten days perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Have you any idea how soon she was able to get out of bed? After ten days you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh yes, but I think she was out of bed before that you know but not for ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 But for the whole day it would be after about ten days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 She lived at her home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 So they looked after her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes, with her mother and father - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did she have a nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Yes. A very capable country woman - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would her parents look after the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh quite a lot - yes. In fact they idolised the baby - spoilt her nearly - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 The nurse wouldn't be there very long would she?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no. Looked in every day for a week or - about a week perhaps I think. Then my wife's sister came home and arranged a hol
iday so that she was there for a fortnight or so - yes, so - all hands on deck you see - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 How much did you have to do with your daughter when she was young - were you able to be with her before she was a year old at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not a great deal, no, because - by the time she was - when she was about six months old I had to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place
}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} again - about five months old perhaps - yes. I had to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever feed her or bath her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh no. Never did anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you change her nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh, never, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you help to get her to sleep? Or attend to her in the night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I - I can't say so because I wasn't often there you see only an odd night now and again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you play with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
As a little girl I think I did, yes, but - as I say she was only about six months old - or five or six months old when I had to go off again to Frances, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And then did you not come back again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Until March 1919 - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 I think you said you were a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Oh quite - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Why do you think you thought that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Well, as I say at school the Economics master used to drill us with the - sort of splendid thing it - what a splendid thing free trade was and that kind of thing - the
 basis of the Liberal - doctrine then - and I was a Liberal there's no doubt about that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What about your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, now it's a funny thing I can't remember much about her politics - I don't think .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Was she interested at all? How would she vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 
Of course they didn't got the vote until well after the first war did they - no. But I rather think she was Conservative - I think so - yes. By that time I think I'd turned a little that way because the Liberals were up and down sort 
of - little bit - you never knew quite where they were - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you vote in a general election before 1919? There was one in 1906.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, that - I was - when I was at school that was - yes. No, that was the big one when the Liberals got in all ov
er the country - yes. No, I was not - of a - still well - a minor then - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party in your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Not in my work - no, no. No, no pressure at all - no, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Were you ever a member of the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And did you ever work for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 And your wife didn't either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did you take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No. I can't say that I did - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 You wouldn't belong to a political club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, nothing like that - no, I never did - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 When you and your wife were not doing your work how did you spend your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, we didn't set up h
ome together until - the later part of 1919 because we couldn't find a house anywhere and - we then found a little furnished cottage at Stoney Stratford which was fifty-one miles from Euston - oh yes, and we had that for nine months - that was our first h
ome - setting up together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What country is that in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Buckinghamshire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 What would you do in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Well, actually there wasn't a great deal of time because - I used to get home something after seven - it was a longish journey
 you see - and - well having played with Joy who was quite a nice little girl and it was her bed time and there wasn't much time after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Would you spend most evenings at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 At home - definitely at home - oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15540585 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 Did either of you go to any clubs or institutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8652529 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid349627\charrsid6631206 No, we were self sufficient - yes. We had some friends down}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11808836\charrsid6631206  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
